-- Indian shares edge higher; tech stocks surge 
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Fri Jan 10, 2014 05:08AM EST
-- None



MUMBAI, Jan 10 (Reuters) - Indian shares provisionally edged up on Friday after earlier hitting their highest intraday level in nearly a week as stocks of software exporters rose after Infosys Ltd's quarterly earnings beat market expectations.

Infosys Ltd <INFY.NS> provisionally rose 3.1 percent, while Tata Consultancy Services Ltd <TCS.NS> ended 2.1 percent higher.